recommend registering with a generic school email addresses if possible,
this is because it means the school will not need to change their initial
admin when a staff member leaves. Once the initial admin has registered
(Through an external provider account Microsoft/Google etc.) and has signed
in they will be able invite additional staff members as an admin.
The site has not synced in 2 years so any new users in this time will not
have pulled through. I have provided some steps to follow below to
hopefully restart the sync: - Open SIMS Services Manager on the SIMS
server. - From the home page, locate the 'SIMS Online Services Client'
package and go into the settings for this package via the 'Actions' column.
- In the Client ID/Secret box, please remove the Client ID and Secret
details and re-add them with what is displayed below (Even if they look the
same): Client ID: ssm-c814f666-2a53-4d2c-bdf2-9152fe4b61c5 Secret:
j7goW8KUfMQEpo7A0lBoUxvkbfUDcFgR - Go back to the SSM homepage and toggle
the SIMS Online Service client package off and then on again. If users are
still not pulling through as expected please let me know. I have attached
the Options Online PDFs to the case. Kind regards,
Josh

Hi Sarah,

This is a reminder for the PSHE Association Spring Conference 2023 taking
place tomorrow morning, 9:30 - 13:00 BST.

*Joining instructions*

To join the conference, use the "Enter Conference" button above.

1. Scroll to the bottom of the conference page, and click into Keynote
Session 1 - Samantha Millar QGM and PSHE Association Chief Executive
Jonathan Baggaley. You may need to click the presentation screen or prompt
to enable audio.
2. When this session is finished, you'll be sent back to the main
conference page, where you can then choose and click to join your first
workshop.
3. After the first workshop there will be a short break, then click into
Keynote Session 2 - Vanita Sundaram, Professor of Education at the
University of York.
4. When this session is finished, you'll be sent back to the main
conference page, where you can then choose and click to join your second
workshop.
5. After the second workshop, click into the final Keynote Session 3 -
Polly Haste, Ofsted joint subject lead for PSHE, RSHE and Citizenship and
Laura Bates, founder of the Everyday Sexism Project.

We will be providing recordings and the slides for all of the workshops and
keynotes which will be available for 30 days following the conference, so
you will have a chance to view workshops you do not attend on the day.
*IT and Tech support*

1. Before the Conference, check with your IT support at school to make sure
that the Big Marker platform is accessible and not blocked by a firewall or
cybersecurity. You can check the BigMarker platform system requirements
here: https://www.bigmarker.com/system_check

From: DfEICT, ConnectTheClassroom <ConnectTheClassroom.DfEICT@education.gov.uk>
Sent: 17 March 2023 07:26
To: Jackie Batley <jackie.batley@woodlesford.leeds.sch.uk>
Subject: Confirmation of Acceptance to Connect the Classroom Programme: Procurement Pack Attached CRM:0465418

In regards to: Woodlesford Primary School 

Dear  Jackie Batley,


Regarding your recent application for Connect the Classroom funding, we are pleased to confirm that following a review of the information you submitted regarding your ICT infrastructure in school, we will be able to support you in carrying out upgrades. Based on the information supplied, our suggested schedule of items to be funded is as follows:

  *   Core Network Switches
  *   Edge Switches with Power Over Ethernet and MultiGig capability to connect these to your network
  *   Wireless Access Points
  *   This is in addition to the installation and handover of that equipment

Please note, there are a number of reasons why what you finally need might differ from the above.

The solution presented to DfE should be for campus-wide WiFi coverage and as such quantities may differ to what you currently have installed.

We attach a procurement pack for you school containing several attachments.

What to do next

  *   Before proceeding further, we recommend that you speak with your ICT Support provider about the scope of work in your setting.
  *   You will need to issue copies of the attached Procurement Pack to your potential suppliers.
  *   Once you have a quotation that you are ready to proceed with, please return the completed Document 3 Cost Matrix to us along with all supporting documentation from your chosen supplier. Return all documents to the mailbox address along with your URN in the subject line.
  *   Do not raise a Purchase Order or confirm works until we issue you with authorisation to proceed. Your grant payment is only guaranteed after you have received a funding approval letter from us.

Help?

  *   Webinars are running to go through the above, step by step, with the opportunity to ask questions. You will find a link to join them in the instructions or contact us for an invitation.
  *   If you need any advice, contact us at: ConnectTheClassroom.DfEICT@education.gov.uk<mailto:ConnectTheClassroom.DfEICT@education.gov.uk>
  *   If you need assistance in finding suitable suppliers, please contact us. We are unable to recommend specific suppliers to you but can direct you to places where you can find potential ones.
  *   If a supplier has a question about the requirements, you can direct them to us for clarification. Please ask them to include your URN ( 107834 ) in the subject line of any email they send to us so that we know which school they are asking about. There are also webinars for suppliers and a link is included in their instructions document in the pack.

Regards

Connect the Classroom Programme Team ¦ Department for Education

fixed music suite?

Frequently Asked Questions

Where can I find out more about how to perform the installation?

Installation instructions for SIMS Options Online can be downloaded here
<https://myaccount.capita-cs.co.uk/Search/DownloadDocument?s=ResourceID-1-5660>.

Installation instructions for SIMS Parent Lite can be downloaded here
<http://simspublications.com/876223/assets/simsparentinstall.pdf>.

The instructions provide step-by-step details for the installation of this
service. We strongly recommend that they are forwarded onto your school IT
contact.

Do I have to perform the installation all in one go?

No, you can stop and start the installation again at any time. If you have
already registered you can go straight back to the admin portal
<https://admin.sims.co.uk/> with the account you used to register with us
originally.

What if I opted in for a remote installation and overview by ESS?

For schools who have opted in for a remote install and overview, please
await contact from a member of our Professional Services team for next
steps.

What if I am a Hosted SIMS school?

For Hosted SIMS schools, please begin the installation process as described
in the documentation and log a case with the service desk when you are
ready for the technical installation to take place.

I have a SIMS ID username/password from another product. Can I use this?

We don't currently support using existing SIMS ID username/passwords for
system onboarding. Please use another supported account type, such as
Office 365 or Google.

Who should I contact for support?

If you have any questions about the installation process or are not sure
about something, please log a support case with your support unit.

From: Chantelle Tuitt <Chantelle.Tuitt@cla.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 7 Mar 2023 at 15:23
Subject: Copyright Royalties Data Collection- PaperCut Copy Button
Configuration
To: swillsden@ahs.pmat.academy <swillsden@ahs.pmat.academy>
Cc: Kate Jackson <Kate.Jackson@cla.co.uk>


Dear Sam,



I write with reference to the recent data collection briefing with my
colleague Kate Jackson and understand that the school wishes to utilise the
CLA Copy button in  PaperCut MF during the exercise.  As the data
collection starts early next term, it’s important that the CLA Copy button
is installed at the earliest opportunity and certainly before the end of
this term, so we can ensure everything is working as it should.  The button
is a great way to send us your data so below are the set-up essentials
needed to get the ball rolling:



*Installing and configuring the button*

The CLA Copy button works in MF version 21.0 or later and, if running site
servers, 22.0 or later.  We recommend you check with your PaperCut provider
if there are any questions as to the MF status at the school. Once a
version check has been done, the CLA connector should be installed on the
same server as PaperCut MF.  The instructions for this can be found in the
document *CLA-PaperCut* *Integration Guide*, attached to this email.



An important part of the integration is to include the three pieces of
unique identifying information which we provide.  This allows CLA to
understand where the data has come from and ensure a secure end to end
transfer process.  Page 3 of the Integration Guide shows where these
details are required, with the specifics for your school provided on the
attached document, *Unique ID Details.*  It is important that only
CLA-provided details are entered in these three fields otherwise the data
will not reach our Azure data lake correctly and the installation will need
to be reconfigured.



*Test Scan *

Once you have completed the installation, the next step is to send us a
test scan using the CLA Copy button.  Once this scan has been sent please
drop me a short email confirming as such, including the date and time it
was sent.  Once successfully received I will confirm and, if there are any
issues which require further intervention, I will advise on next steps.



If you have any questions about any of the above, please do get in touch by
email or phone.  We will always endeavour to assist with the more common
issues we come across though there are occasions when we may need to
involve your PaperCut provider.  I will let you know if that is the case.



You now have all the essentials for setting up the CLA Copy button so thank
you for helping us to support the rights holders and I look forward to
hearing from you.







*Best wishes*



*Chantelle Tuitt*

Dear Ms Bedford,

Thank you for your email.

I am writing to confirm our virtual meeting on Tuesday 7th March 2023 at 12
o’clock to discuss the forthcoming collection of royalties data which will
take place between 24th April to 11th July 2023.  These dates are fixed in
order to ensure a robust sample.

During the meeting, discussions will focus on preparing for the exercise,
how we capture data, communications and support materials.  Given there
will be no on-site visits we will need to ensure staff are aware of their
role and obligations during the exercise.  I will also be demonstrating our
intuitive online data tool, My Content.

I anticipate we will need no more than 30 minutes and, of course, I will be
more than happy to address any queries you and colleagues may have.

Could you please provide the following in advance of our meeting,

  *   Photocopier/MFD location details (I believe you have 2).

  *   A direct dial phone number in case of computer gremlins on the day!

login EVERYTIME. This means that despite Papercut having the card
information stored the users are loosing time and also print jobs unless
they stay on one printer manufacturer.

> We are now integrating CPOMS with SIMS via Groupcall's Xporter on Demand
> (XoD) platform. Please use the following link to begin your setup with the
> XoD platform:
>
>
> https://sentamu.cpoms.net/schools/1/xod/new
>
>
> Please complete the details and click on the Submit button. The School
> Contact will then receive an email detailing the next steps. You will need
> to authorise CPOMS access to your XoD install.
>
>
> There are two options to select when it comes to installing XoD
> components; 'Self Setup' or 'Book a slot'. We advise to select Book a slot
> as Groupcall will help you with the installation process (please check with
> your technical contact that they will be available).
>
>
> Once that’s all done, you can log in to your XoD account (
> https://manage.groupcall.com) and review the data being sent to CPOMS.
>
>
> Following the move to XoD integration, your Student Groups on CPOMS will
> be re-created. As a result, if you have Restrict Access enabled for your
> groups (or automatic alerts configured), you may need to reconfigure this
> following the first import.
>
>
> You will also need to update the Main group type and Dashboard group type
> settings found in Admin > Settings to reflect the new groups from Xporter
> on Demand. The reason the grouping name changes is to avoid any duplication
> of student groups.
>
>
> Finally, certain areas of data will not be pulled across - medical notes
> being the most notable. If you actively use medical notes, you may wish to
> wait for the upgrade and/or find an alternative method of updating CPOMS
> with this information.
>
>

Why DMARC reporting is important

DMARC reporting in Mail Check helps assess if emails being sent from your
domains are trusted as legitimate by recipients, based on the anti-spoofing
controls SPF, DKIM and DMARC. The feature provides both interactive email
traffic graphs, as well as our ‘Insights’ feature that will do some of the
analysis for you.

If these anti-spoofing controls are not implemented correctly your domain
is open to abuse from fake emails, and you may have issues with legitimate
emails being sent to spam folders.

How to set up DMARC reporting

There are two key actions to set up DMARC reporting in Mail Check. The
example below is specific to yorkhigh.southbank.academy. Both actions
require making small changes to your DNS record.

Note that DMARC reporting and asset verification will also cover subdomains
of yorkhigh.southbank.academy unless you decide to configure subdomains
separately.

Hi Vital team

Just to flag up something I’d spoken to Lewis about today and he suggested I raise it via this route.

As you know York Learning have an office at Huntington School from which aspects of our community provision operate. There has been an issue with the phones there for some time – I have spoken to CYC tech support and they say it is in your field not theirs as it is within the school.

The team working there answer the main York Learning numbers via a hunt group/Skype method – if they are logged into their CYC accounts the phone ‘rings’ and they can answer the call using headsets.

They have reported that approx. 50% of the time when they answer the call will terminate without connecting them to the person who has made the call.

Similarly, outward calls, although a better success rate, often do not connect and just drop out without warning.

We are getting a lot of pushback from learners saying they are unable to get through on the phone and/or they are having the phone put down on them, which isn’t true – but obviously it is cutting off and they are interpreting that as we’re doing it deliberately.

There was no pattern to this, apart from today – where it was noticeably better. It was raised that this was a staff training day in the school. The two things may be entirely unconnected but it has occurred to me that perhaps there is some kind of throttle/upper limit which means that on a regular day the calls are not getting through because of regular activity within the school meaning there is no capacity for the Skype call to connect through the system.

Would you be able to have a look and investigate if this is the case or there is some other reason why the calls keep dropping out, and if you can find a problem look at ways of sorting it, please? We get a significant amount of our bookings via phone especially for courses in the Wider Community Learning aspect of our offer and if we cannot rely on the phone connection not only does it cause immense frustration both to staff and learners, including much time spent having to placate people who have got in touch to complain they cannot get through, we are missing out on valuable revenue as people cannot get through to book and go elsewhere.

If you want to speak to me about this happy to have a chat – 07887 545795 – but it might also be worth speaking to Sarah Hammond, who works for me and is the Centre Co-Ordinator for the Huntington School site and is the team leader there. She’s experiencing it day to day. Sarah.hammond@york.gov.uk is her email.

Thank you very much for any help and guidance you can provide.

Will Harris| Digital Skills Curriculum Manager & Operations Manager
t: 07887 545795 & 01904 552905 | e:will.harris@york.gov.uk

To: Graham School <e.robins@gra.hlt.academy>


In regards to: Graham School

Dear Emma Robins,

Regarding your recent application for Connect the Classroom funding, we are
pleased to confirm that following a review of the information you submitted
regarding your ICT infrastructure in school, we will be able to support you
in carrying out upgrades. Based on the information supplied, our suggested
schedule of items to be funded is as follows:


   - Core Network Switches
   - Edge Switches with Power Over Ethernet and MultiGig capability to
   connect these to your network
   - Wireless Access Points
   - This is in addition to the installation and handover of that equipment

Please note, there are a number of reasons why what you finally need might
differ from the above.

The solution presented to DfE should be for campus-wide WiFi coverage and
as such quantities may differ to what you currently have installed.

We attach a procurement pack for you school containing several attachments.
What to do next

   - Before proceeding further, we recommend that you speak with your ICT
   Support provider about the scope of work in your setting.
   - You will need to issue copies of the attached Procurement Pack to your
   potential suppliers.
   - Once you have a quotation that you are ready to proceed with, please
   return the completed Document 3 Cost Matrix to us along with all supporting
   documentation from your chosen supplier. Return all documents to the
   mailbox address along with your URN in the subject line.
   - *Do not raise a Purchase Order or confirm works until we issue you
   with authorisation to proceed*. Your grant payment is only guaranteed
   after you have received a funding approval letter from us.

Help?

   - Webinars are running to go through the above, step by step, with the
   opportunity to ask questions. You will find a link to join them in the
   instructions or contact us for an invitation.
   - If you need any advice, contact us at:
   ConnectTheClassroom.DfEICT@education.gov.uk
   - If you need assistance in finding suitable suppliers, please contact
   us. We are unable to recommend specific suppliers to you but can direct you
   to places where you can find potential ones.
   - If a supplier has a question about the requirements, you can direct
   them to us for clarification. Please ask them to include your URN ( 146769
   ) in the subject line of any email they send to us so that we know which
   school they are asking about. There are also webinars for suppliers and a
   link is included in their instructions document in the pack.

Regards

Connect the Classroom Programme Team ¦ Department for Education

[required] Title: Printing to incorrect printers and potential GDPR issues- IMPORTANT
Description:
Good afternoon, this morning I found a copy of a printed student “passport”
on the printer in G2. This is a confidential document to that child.

I went to find the  SENDCO, who said she had sent it to the SEN printer on
the drop-down list. I also know that the printer in G2 is not listed on the
Chromebooks as G2, instead it is listed as G5. I only know this after a
passing conversation with Chris the yesterday- do other staff know?

If staff cannot be certain that the printer that they are sending
information to is the correct printer, then we could very easily have
potential breaches of data. Not only this, at present staff will be wasting
precious time looking for what they have printed and potentially thinking
that it has go lost in the ”ether” and print again; compounding the issue
even more.

Can this be looked into as soon as possible. I would not like there to be
an incident of something confidential being printed, only to find that
confidence is broken.

I do appreciate how busy you all are at present, but this is something that
should not be overlooked.

Thank you

Ed
